ss=title>   Guild Organization - What format do you have?</span><hr size=1> Brigade has a single Commander that can &quot;make the law&quot; if needed, but has only done so on about three occasions.  After that we have 4 Generals and Colonels that can also make fairly strong statements about what the rules of the guild are, but seldom do.  Next we have the Officers.  About 1/4 of the guild are officers.  In this we have House Elders.  The leader of each house (Class) that is responsible for helping build the toons of that class.  This done by working epics, helping find the next good armor piece or weapon upgrade etc. (I am House Elder for the House of Death - Necromancers).  We have Raid leaders who are tasked with building Raid Events.  We have a &quot;Force Recon&quot; that is tasked with going to new zones and learning the layout and being able to provide scouting information on a zone.<br>
<br>
We do not charge a Guild Tax, but do ask for donations (Peridots looted are usually put in the guild bank for raids for example and some raids are for guildbank cash exclusively).<br>
<br>
We are 65 % Family 35% raid at this time.<br>
<br>
So that said....  What is your base structure?  Do you have a &quot;Tax&quot;.  I want to see how others are organized and debate a bit of pros and cons of each structure.<br>
<br>
