<br>
2 guild leaders<br>
<br>
An Investigations officer (dealt with problems between outsiders of the guild, and insiders by harvesting information).<br>
<br>
A strategy team (to find out how to kill new mobs, and learn form our mistakes)<br>
<br>
A recruitment department.<br>
<br>
Raid leaders.<br>
<br>
Administrative officers.<br>
<br>
Guild banker.<br>
<br>
etc.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mixylplix>mixylplix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Brigade - Guild Rep</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(10/29/03 2:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1106.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild Organization - What format do you have?</span><hr size=1> Jeshter.  For the &quot;information Gathering&quot; part for some reason they picked me to do that.  I guess I am just sneaky or people trust me but for the two Court Martials they dragged me into the fact finder role.  We have not needed this to be formal yet.  We have only had a couple issues withoutsiders causing us crap and we tend to take care of that IMEMDIATELY in game.  Some picks on a lowbie they have 5 officers around them in minutes taking &quot;care&quot; of the situation.  Beyond issues with Necrobabe and Waango most of you dealings have been positive lately.  Even in a potentially contensious issue last night with another guild crashing our Paul Caverns camp we just sat down and worked it out.  They were PLing a LOW toon (Don't people understand that being PL'd means your skills SUCK and you fizzle and miss on attacks????)  But we wroked it out, gave them a tent and a side pop to keep and we had plenty for our full group to deal with.  An unguilded toon in our group got pissy and left.  He did not like it that we were talking to the other people.  Glad he left.  A bard trying to tank with a Pally and SK there was stupid and he was a &quot;bleeder&quot; for the cleric to deal with.  At least the ranger stayed back used arrows and came in after agro was built.  Smart player.  Smart Chanter too.  Good group.  Man I love a good group.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Mixyplix Targeth<br>
House Elder - House of Death<br>
Brigade Guild Representative</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=o8ithefitzi8o>O8I The Fitz I8O</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(10/29/03 2:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1106.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild Organization - What format do you have?</span><hr size=1> Clan X has a guild leader, officers, and members as the basic hierarchal leadership structure.  However, Clan X has teams which have deligated power.  For example, we have a loot team, End Game Team, Recruit team, ect.  Everyone in the guild has the oppurtunity to belong to any of these teams.<br>
<br>
Further detail on the responsibilities and roles for these things can be found here:<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqclanx.com/Roles.htm" target="top">www.eqclanx.com/Roles.htm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
and here:<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqclanx.com/CharterX.htm" target="top">www.eqclanx.com/CharterX.htm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
We have no required tax.  If we require something, like items for bane weapons or components for a key quest, then we sometimes have events to obtain these items.  Items that are in the bank for a long period of time get sold in the bazaar.  We encourage people to help out fellow guildmembers and to contribute as much to the guild as they can. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dennin>Dennin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dallow Abligo - Guild Rep</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(10/29/03 2:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1106.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild Organization - What format do you have?</span><hr size=1> Well, our is real short and simple.  We have 2 GL tags, tho both are help by 1 person.  Sorta like the president (or should be...but wont go into THAT here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) she comes up with ideas for rules, raids, etc.  The officers (only about 6) say yea or nay... if majority goes, its law.  The entire guild always has a say.. so all ideas are given hearing, but it comes down to the GL and officers to make it rule.  As for a tax, we don't have any.  However, all raids we do, all gems, cash, and &quot;vendor loot&quot; goes to our guild bank (GL has a toon set aside for just this).  Doing it that way, we have always been able to affor dot's, pearls, air and hate stones.  All loot is NBG, and always goes to people that attended...if no one needs then we sell for guild <p>You go ahead of me, we let you die.<br>
If I don't call assist, watch me die like an idiot.<br>
<br>
http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=718366</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seerfamily>Seer Family</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seer Family...<br>
Gotta catch 'em all!</span><br>  Posts: 686<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(10/29/03 3:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1106.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild Organization - What format do you have?</span><hr size=1> 3 guild leader tags, but one formal guild leader, at this time the other 2 are considered respected elders and leave decisions to the primary GL. In the past when the guild has gone through growth spurts and periods when we were raiding a lot, we have had 2 and even at one time 3 active Leaders.<br>
1 primarily responsible for 46+ level folks and their activities and 1 primarily for the low end folks and the third acted as mediary in the event that the leadership needed to make a policy decision.<br>
<br>
Active officers<br>
<br>
Raid Coordinator<br>
<br>
Treasurer<br>
<br>
Web master<br>
<br>
Judiciary officer - appointed as needed<br>
<br>
Inactive retired officers generally keep officer tag as long as they are playing and are treated with respect for their period of service as an active officer. We also generally allow them to resume active officer status as long as they make an effort to catch up on current guild status.<br>
<br>
We generally speaking do not split loot on raids, it all goes to the guild bank except for no drop items or items which could immediately benefit some deserving individual NBG. <br>
On occasion preannounced we also occasionally split loot with raid party, after expenses, such as dots and port components.<br>
<br>
Our structure over the years has remained pretty flexible. Because we have at times had as many as over 100 active members total roster over 300 and as few as 9 active when I agreed to be guild leader.<br>
Obviously when I had 9 active members our officer needs were different from when we decided to create a raiding guild apart from the main guild. At that point we had over 100 active members with 40 of them planable. At that point I decided we needed that third Leader tag.<br>
<br>
Flexibility has kep our lil family style guild alive, through loss due to poaching, seasonal slow downs, new games, and drama queens. <p>Shariona  56 Cleric  Circle of Virtue<br>
<br>
Toric  48 Paladin and Elder Circle of Virtue<br>
<br>
Aideen     22 Druid<br>
